1
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,200
Doctor, how is she?

2
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:56,840
The patient's condition suddenly worsened during the surgery.

3
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,720
I'm afraid

4
00:01:58,039 --> 00:02:00,040
she won't make it through the night.

5
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Yuanbao.

6
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,440
Grandma, I'm here.

7
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,280
Grandma.

8
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:33,000
I promised Mom and Dad

9
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:35,320
to take good care of you.

10
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,120
You also promised me

11
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,320
that when I get married,

12
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,000
you'd help me dress up.

13
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,490
And when I have children in the future,

14
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,800
you'd help me take care of them.

15
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,920
We agreed.

16
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:57,520
You will live a long life.

17
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,560
You will always stay with me.

18
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,560
Grandma.

19
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,720
When you get better,

20
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:09,120
I'll go home for dinner.

21
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:13,160
I still want to eat the spare ribs you make.

22
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,880
Yuanbao.

23
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,360
Let go of the past.

24
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,720
Cherish what you have.

25
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,320
Be grateful.

26
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,880
Live a good life.

27
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,200
Grandma loves you.

28
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,440
Grandma will be in heaven,

29
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,720
staying by your side,

30
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,160
and blessing you.

31
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,960
No, Grandma.

32
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,920
Mom and Dad are already gone.

33
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:50,560
Don't leave Yuanbao behind.

34
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,360
Grandma!

35
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,080
Grandma!

36
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,120
Grandma!

37
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,360
Grandma!

38
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:18,959
Grandma!

39
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,079
Then when I get married...

40
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,200
You have to dress me up

41
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,160
and make me look beautiful.

42
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:28,760
Okay.

43
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:33,200
I'm just looking forward to the day you find happiness.

44
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:52,880
No!

45
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,560
Where are you taking my grandma?

46
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:58,920
Where are you taking her?

47
00:04:58,960 --> 00:04:59,800
Yuanbao.

48
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,480
Your grandma won't rest in peace if you act like this.

49
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,440
You can't be like this.

50
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,800
Let go, Yuanbao.

51
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,240
Grandma!

52
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,760
Please let go, Yuanbao.

53
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,240
Doctor.

54
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:15,000
Doctor, please save my grandma.

55
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,200
I'm begging you, save my grandma.

56
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,640
My grandma is not dead.

57
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,680
She is not dead yet.

58
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:25,010
My grandma said she would wait for me to come home for dinner.

59
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:28,080
The dead cannot be brought back to life. My condolences.

60
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,520
My grandma is all I have.

61
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,320
Let go, child.

62
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:40,760
Mutou.

63
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,800
Yuanbao, Yuanbao.

64
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,920
She's too emotional.

65
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,850
Hurry, take her to the ward to rest.

66
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:56,400
Mom, what are you guys doing?

67
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,360
Why are you just coming back now?

68
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:02,840
Who is that?

69
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:07,490
I'm asking you, who is that?

70
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,560
It's Grandma.

71
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,120
Grandma...

72
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,160
My child.

73
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,520
Grandma, I'm back.

74
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,520
Grandma.

75
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,840
I won the prize money.

76
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:32,040
I can pay for your treatment.

77
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,159
You'll get better after the surgery.

78
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,120
Grandma,

79
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:41,280
you promised Yuanbao you'd take care of her forever.

80
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,240
Didn't you?

81
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,800
Grandma!

82
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,680
Grandma,

83
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,080
look at me.

84
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,880
My child, don't be like this.

85
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:55,120
Grandma won't rest in peace if you do.

86
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,240
My child.

87
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,720
Grandma!

88
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:01,480
I won the prize money.

89
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,640
I can pay for your treatment and surgery.

90
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,040
Grandma,

91
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:08,480
look at me.

92
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,440
Yuanbao,

93
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,320
you're awake.

94
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,800
The doctor said you were overly grieved

95
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,760
and physically exhausted.

96
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,860
I've asked Ms. Tian for leave for you.

97
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,440
Get some good rest.

98
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:03,920
Yuanbao,

99
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,820
grandma's funeral arrangements

100
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,850
will be handled by your aunt and me.

101
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,360
Take good care of yourself,

102
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,840
so she won't worry about you.

103
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:27,400
Qingyun,

104
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,960
your dad and I

105
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:31,090
need to take care of grandma's funeral

106
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,570
and look after Yuanbao.

107
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,000
You've been tired for days,

108
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,799
go home and rest.

109
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:38,880
We've got this.

110
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,600
Green garlic is quite expensive nowadays.

111
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,920
Time to eat.

112
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,280
Grandma.

113
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:18,320
Qingyun.

114
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,320
Qingyun.

115
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,480
How are the school procedures going?

116
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:16,680
Both kids' previous applications were rejected.

117
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:20,120
I just faxed over the documents of Qingyun's

118
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:22,560
national physics competition award.

119
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,520
Let's wait and see.

120
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,330
What about Yuanbao?

121
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,650
Let's try our best for both.

122
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,640
We can't miss such a good opportunity.

123
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,880
I hope there will be two spots.

124
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,280
There must be two spots.

125
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:51,520
This child

126
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,520
hasn't slept well for days.

127
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,360
Don't wake him up.

128
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:33,080
Grandma.

129
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,520
Grandma, you must live a long life

130
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,120
and stay with me forever.

131
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:03,560
Okay, Grandma will live a long life

132
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:06,160
and stay with you forever.

133
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,240
Come on, Yuanbao.

134
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:25,960
You are the best.

135
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,040
Yuanbao,

136
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,360
come on.

137
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,760
You are the best.

138
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:44,760
Grandma,

139
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:50,800
we are going home.

140
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:26,640
Yuanbao, will you come to the UK with us?

141
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,720
To study abroad with Qingyun.

142
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,680
We've looked into it.

143
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:36,480
You can take a one-year foundation course first,

144
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:37,680
and then apply for university.

145
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:38,610
I'm not leaving.

146
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,600
Why?

147
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,400
I can't leave my grandma behind.

148
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:51,480
Yuanbao.

149
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,640
I understand how you feel,

150
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,020
but the dead cannot come back to life.

151
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,640
The living

152
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:07,160
must live well for those who have passed.

153
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:09,080
I think your parents

154
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:12,360
and your grandma in heaven

155
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,400
would want you to be with us.

156
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,160
I know that in your heart,

157
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,420
you've never forgiven your uncle and me.

158
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,880
I also know that

159
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,760
if it weren't for us,

160
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:35,170
your family wouldn't have ended up like this.

161
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:42,880
It was right in this room

162
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,700
that your uncle and I knelt before your grandma,

163
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:51,180
confessing and asking for her forgiveness.

164
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,760
Grandma, she...

165
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,320
knew.

166
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:04,680
We came to tell her after it happened,

167
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:07,040
but she already knew by then.

168
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:13,240
Grandma did all this

169
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,800
for me.

170
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:21,880
Silly child.

171
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:25,010
You could say it was for you,

172
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:27,520
but mostly, she wanted us who are still alive

173
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,640
to live well, my child.

174
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:33,320
Before your father died,

175
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:37,360
he told your Uncle Mu,

176
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:41,720
"Take care of my mom and Yuanbao for me.

177
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:48,360
Don't tell the children about today's accident."

178
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,520
Grandma.

179
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:55,800
Mom and Dad.

180
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:58,240
Don't worry.

181
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:01,040
I will live well

182
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,250
so you won't worry about me.

183
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,080
But

184
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:08,760
I can't drag down Qingyun's family anymore.

185
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,400
You are right.

186
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:13,120
It was an accident.

187
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,160
No one is to blame.

188
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:18,120
Auntie.

189
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:21,680
You should go.

190
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,320
I won't leave.

191
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,400
I am grown up now.

192
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:28,800
I can be independent.

193
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:31,560
You don't need to worry about me.

194
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:35,840
I hope Mutou can have a better life.

195
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:38,200
But you alone.

196
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,640
I don't hate you anymore,

197
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:40,600
really.

198
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:43,960
I just

199
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:47,040
can't bear to leave my mom and dad,

200
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,120
and my grandma.

201
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,600
My home is here.

202
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,720
This is my home.

203
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:01,480
So I won't go abroad.

204
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:07,760
Yuanbao.

205
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:31,650
What do you mean there's only one quota for studying abroad?

206
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,700
Since there is only one quota,

207
00:19:33,760 --> 00:19:34,960
why bother?

208
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:36,040
I,

209
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:36,720
we,

210
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:37,480
why don't

211
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:39,440
we just stay in China?

212
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:40,840
Why must we go to the UK?

213
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,520
I talked to Yuanbao too.

214
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:47,130
She can take a one-year foundation course first.

215
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,000
But she,

216
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:52,700
she absolutely refused to go.

217
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:56,240
But this is too important to you.

218
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,680
If you graduate from that university,

219
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:00,480
your future will be boundless.

220
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:03,040
This is the most important thing in your life.

221
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,480
What about Yuanbao?

222
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:07,180
Grandma just passed away.

223
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,160
If we leave too,

224
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:11,520
are we going to leave her here alone?

225
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:12,540
I don't want to.

226
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:13,800
Son.

227
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,360
We really have no choice.

228
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,210
We really can't get two quotas.

229
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,080
Otherwise,

230
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:21,600
we wouldn't leave Yuanbao behind.

231
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:23,840
Mom, Dad,

232
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:24,760
believe me.

233
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:26,340
Even if I stay in China,

234
00:20:26,360 --> 00:20:28,200
I can definitely get into a very good university

235
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,440
and have a bright future.

236
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,960
Why do we have to go to the UK?

237
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:32,400
Isn't our country good enough?

238
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,800
Foreign countries are nowhere near as good as ours.

239
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,480
Besides, we absolutely cannot leave.

240
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:38,280
If we really leave, what about Yuanbao?

241
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:39,210
She's all alone.

242
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:41,640
Why are you so stubborn?

243
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,570
We didn't say we'd never come back.

244
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:46,240
As long as you're on holiday,

245
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,040
I promise you,

246
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:48,960
whether it's winter or summer vacation,

247
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,560
we will come back to see her.

248
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:53,200
Besides, if Yuanbao works hard,

249
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,370
she can get into her ideal university.

250
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:57,280
And in less than a year,

251
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:58,480
after a year,

252
00:20:58,480 --> 00:20:59,640
wouldn't the two of you

253
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,760
go your separate ways to university anyway?

254
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,400
That's different, Mom.

255
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:04,520
I told Yuanbao that

256
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:05,840
we are family.

257
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:08,180
Now we're leaving her here alone.

258
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:09,680
Her grandma passed away,

259
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:11,120
Grandpa Gong went to the nursing home,

260
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:12,180
and we're not here.

261
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,200
She's just a girl,

262
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,320
all alone here.

263
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:15,320
If she gets sick

264
00:21:15,320 --> 00:21:17,120
or has an accident, who will take care of her?

265
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:18,840
How can you be so cruel?

266
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,200
Cruel?

267
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,080
We tried our best

268
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:24,690
to fight for quotas for you.

269
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,880
If you hadn't won the physics competition,

270
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,740
you wouldn't be able to go either.

271
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,160
For Yuanbao,

272
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,840
your father and I have done our best

273
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:34,560
and given her everything.

274
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:36,280
For Grandma's medical bills,

275
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:36,680
we...

276
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:37,440
Qiuling.

277
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:38,680
Qiuling.

278
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,800
Even if we go abroad,

279
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:45,880
your father and I

280
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,400
will find a way to leave Yuanbao

281
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:48,720
enough money for food

282
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:50,480
and tuition.

283
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:52,200
What else do you want us to do

284
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,640
to satisfy you?

285
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:59,960
Mom, you said it yourself before.

286
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,920
Yuanbao is your own daughter.

287
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:05,210
Have you forgotten?

288
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,840
Now you're leaving her here all alone.

289
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:13,200
If it weren't for Uncle Xiong and the others back then...

290
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:15,280
Would I be the one left behind now?

291
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:16,240
You...

292
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:18,280
How can you two be so ungrateful?

293
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:20,480
Enough.

294
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,760
Child, how can you talk like that?

295
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:27,210
How can you speak to your parents this way?

296
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:28,960
You are right.

297
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:32,940
If it weren't for your Uncle Xiong back then,

298
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:35,240
you would be the one left behind now.

299
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:36,880
But even so,

300
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:40,300
just because we feel guilty towards you,

301
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:43,560
shouldn't Yuanbao have a better future?

302
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,000
Without Yuanbao.

303
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,520
A future?

304
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,860
How can there be a good future?

305
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,160
Honey.

306
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:08,560
Don't be mad.

307
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:10,440
I'll go check on him.

308
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:12,640
If worse comes to worst, we'll find another way.

309
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:14,040
Get some rest first.

310
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:15,720
Qingyun.

311
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:17,640
Qingyun.

312
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:21,440
Qingyun.

313
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:32,560
We've lived here for 20 years.

314
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:36,280
Yeah, it's getting old.

315
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:38,570
When your mom and I got married,

316
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,000
we lived here.

317
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:43,500
We were neighbors with the Xiongs back then.

318
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:47,120
In a blink of an eye, 20 years have passed.

319
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:49,730
Unfortunately,

320
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:51,680
it won't be long

321
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:53,980
before this is no longer our home.

322
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:01,040
What do you mean?

323
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:07,280
To pay for Yuanbao's grandmother's medical bills,

324
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:08,610
your mom sold the house.

325
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:14,880
We have to move out early next month.

326
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:20,520
I know

327
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,080
you have some complaints

328
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:24,720
about your mom.

329
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,400
But son,

330
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:29,890
anyone in this world

331
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:32,880
can complain about her and misunderstand her,

332
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,440
except for you.

333
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:37,020
You were five that year

334
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:40,570
and suddenly got acute pneumonia.

335
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:43,240
To take care of you,

336
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:46,280
your mom and I had to

337
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:49,080
temporarily switch shifts with Mr. Xiong and his wife.

338
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:50,740
After the accident happened,

339
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,240
I had to handle their funerals

340
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:56,400
and take care of Yuanbao and her grandmother.

341
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:59,120
At the same time, I had to keep working to earn money.

342
00:25:59,120 --> 00:26:00,680
I simply had no time

343
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,640
to go to the hospital to take care of you.

344
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:06,360
So your mom stayed in the hospital alone

345
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:10,250
and took care of you round the clock for over half a month.

346
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:12,210
During that half month,

347
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:14,080
she lost over ten pounds.

348
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,250
She was completely exhausted.

349
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:22,680
Later,

350
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:25,330
to support two kids and an elderly,

351
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:28,600
I had to go on business trips frequently

352
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,320
to earn more money.

353
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:33,340
So the heavy burden of taking care of you guys

354
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,480
fell on your mom's shoulders.

355
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:40,280
Before she married me and gave birth to you,

356
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,760
she couldn't even boil noodles without burning the pot.

357
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:44,880
But for our family,

358
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:47,600
she forced herself to learn everything.

359
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:59,480
She might not be an excellent woman,

360
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:00,880
but

361
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,360
she is truly an excellent mother.

362
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,360
For so many years,

363
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,200
your mom and I

364
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,600
have always felt guilty

365
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:17,540
trying to repay the Xiong family.

366
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:19,720
We really tried our best.

367
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,040
Choosing to go abroad now

368
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,640
is because as your parents,

369
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:29,960
we hope to do what we can

370
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:32,140
to give you a better environment.

371
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,660
But in the current situation,

372
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:37,600
we really can't afford it.

373
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:44,280
Going abroad doesn't mean I'll definitely be successful.

374
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:46,120
We can stay in the country.

375
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:47,540
It's really good here.

376
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:48,360
Son,

377
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:51,220
we almost don't even have a place to live now.

378
00:27:51,480 --> 00:27:53,740
Do you want us to live at Yuanbao's house?

379
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:56,040
She knows the truth now.

380
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:58,600
Tell me,

381
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,480
how can we act like nothing happened

382
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:04,140
and continue to live with her?

383
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:09,720
It's all my fault.

384
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,160
If I were more capable,

385
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:17,050
we wouldn't have to make such a difficult choice.

386
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:27,850
Dad, I'm sorry, Dad.

387
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:29,240
I'm sorry.

388
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,800
You must be tired. Get some rest early.

389
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:53,560
Qingyun has to go to school tomorrow morning.

390
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:54,440
Go to sleep.

391
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:07,040
I'm sorry.

392
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:12,240
But I...

393
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:17,240
I'm sorry.

394
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:22,360
Son.

395
00:29:24,600 --> 00:29:26,240
Does your face still hurt?

396
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:32,600
Mom is also sorry.

397
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:38,000
I've thought it through.

398
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:41,920
You decide whether you want to go or not.

399
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:45,360
If you decide not to go,

400
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,480
your dad will come back to look for a job.

401
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:52,960
As long as our family is together,

402
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:57,240
we can live a good life.

403
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:34,560
I'm sorry.

404
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:51,160
Hello. Table for one?

405
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:53,760
I'm expecting a friend.

406
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:54,600
He'll be here soon.

407
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,800
Okay. Please take a seat.

408
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:56,440
Okay.

409
00:31:29,080 --> 00:31:30,880
Happy birthday, Ruirui.

410
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:50,320
Ruirui.

411
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,960
My mom is quite strict

412
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,200
with my pocket money.

413
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,320
So for your birthday,

414
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:57,040
I could only make you a bowl of longevity noodles.

415
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:57,680
Um...

416
00:31:58,880 --> 00:31:59,920
Don't be picky.

417
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:02,600
Why would I?

418
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:05,010
I love eating noodles the most.

419
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:07,160
Try it.

420
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:19,720
Is it good?

421
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:22,000
It is.

422
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:23,570
It's really delicious.

423
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:25,460
Really delicious.

424
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:28,360
According to you,

425
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,570
not only can I be a singer or a comedian,

426
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,000
but I can also be a chef.

427
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:34,960
You know I'm pretty clumsy.

428
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:38,400
I learned from the chef in the kitchen for a whole day

429
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:40,330
and ruined eight bowls of noodles.

430
00:32:43,120 --> 00:32:43,960
Shang Ningyu,

431
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:45,960
thank you.

432
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:48,480
Since I was born,

433
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,400
this is my first birthday

434
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:54,600
having someone willing to make me longevity noodles by hand.

435
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:58,320
Oh, right.

436
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:05,020
This is for you.

437
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:10,000
I wish you peace every year.

438
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:19,960
What's wrong?

439
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:23,240
Nothing.

440
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:25,720
I'm just really touched.

441
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:28,880
You know

442
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:30,840
my family sells fruit.

443
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:33,200
But ever since I was little,

444
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:34,400
I only ate the rotten

445
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:35,880
and unsellable ones.

446
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:37,980
This is the first time someone gave me

447
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:39,240
such a good

448
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,440
and fresh fruit.

449
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:46,840
Your mom is pretty harsh on you.

450
00:33:48,840 --> 00:33:50,000
Not exactly harsh.

451
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:52,480
It's not easy for my mom to raise me and my sister alone,

452
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:53,340
so she's used to

453
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:55,680
being frugal.

454
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:59,400
You always say your dad is gone.

455
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:02,320
I actually really wanted to ask,

456
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:05,840
how did he pass away?
